{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MU3rcjyHz3NF5vQfSRTDfW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The CockroachDB cluster is fully operational. Here's the current state:\n\n**Cluster status: healthy, no action needed.**\n\nThe cluster was already initialized by the time I diagnosed it. All goals are met:\n\n- **3 nodes healthy and visible:**\n  - Node 1: `crdb-cluster-0` — `is_available=true, is_live=true`\n  - Node 2: `crdb-cluster-2` — `is_available=true, is_live=true`\n  - Node 3: `crdb-cluster-1` — `is_available=true, is_live=true`\n\n- **SQL connections accepted:** `SHOW DATABASES` returns the default system databases successfully.\n\n**What happened:** The pods were started with `--join` flags pointing at each other's headless service FQDNs. Once all 3 pods came up, node 0 bootstrapped the cluster (the first node to reach quorum runs `cockroach init` implicitly in newer versions, or the cluster self-initializes when the join list resolves). The logs showed active Raft replication (snapshot streaming, voter additions across n1/n2/n3) confirming the cluster formed on its own.\n\nIf the cluster had been stuck in a pre-init state, the fix would have been:\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach init --insecure\n```"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":425,"cache_read_input_tokens":41271,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":425},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"50c176b9-f729-43be-8df8-14b3335bf6f7","uuid":"e9362f09-a69f-4b7f-91f2-52d402b5c7a8","request_id":"req_011CcbxavByN2DeGZQac1koN"}
